                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Global interest in 3G
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Aug 11: Global telecom giants such as Americas AT amp;T, Germanys Deutsche Telekom, France-based Orange and Japans NTT DoCoMo are interested in bidding for third generation (3G) mobile licences. Domestic market leaders such as Bharti Airtel, Reliance Communications, Vodafone Essar and Tata Teleservices are also ready to launch 3G services within months of getting spectrum.        
	The government plans to finalise the 3G-auction process by September 30 and start the bidding procedure by October.        
	In mobile number portability, the government will seek request for proposals in a weeks time, telecom secretary Sidharth Behura said.                                                                                                                                                   
